Household is a group of persons living in the same dwelling, in the case where occupant type is residents.

Energy distribution system is a system in charge of delivering the energy inside the building, from the place of energy production to the place of end-use. It consists then in the storage (including battery/tank and pipe volumes), the circulation pumps, the distribution pipes and the end use units (radiators, fan coils etc.).
A usage zone is a zone of a building with homogeneous usage type.
Temperature schedule [C] of the active cooling inside the usage zone.
Temperature schedule [C] of the active heating inside the usage zone.
List of the number of floors part of the usage zone (0 = ground level).
Air change rate [1/h] schedule of the ventilation system inside the usage zone.
One thermal zone may include several usage zones. One usage zone may also include several thermal zones.
Energy Source is the final energy consumed by the energy conversion system.
The rate water vapor is allowed through a surface
The ratio of the total amount of void space in a material (due to poses, small channels, and so on) to the bulk volume occupied by the material.

A thermal zone is a zone of a building which serves as unit for the building heating and cooling simulation. For the simulation, a thermal zone is considered as isothermal. It is a semantic object, which may be or not related to a geometric entity.
Transmission heat loss contribution [W/m.K] of the thermal bridges of the thermal zone shell to the overall UValue.
Thermal capacity [Wh/K] of the zone including the contributing construction layers and zone fournitures.
Air change rate [1/h] due to air leakage of the zone shell.
A building unit is a part of usage zone, such as dwelling or workplace, which is related to a single occupant entity.
Maximum fraction of the related opening which can be covered with the shading device.

Irregular time series is the opposite of a regular time series. The data in the time series follows a temporal sequence, but the measurements might not happen at a regular time interval. http://www-01.ibm.com/support/knowledgecenter/SSCRJU_3.0.0/com.ibm.swg.im.infosphere.streams.timeseries-toolkit.doc/doc/timeseries-regular.html
Percentaged energy reflectance in different wavelength ranges
Application Domain Extension Energy of CityGML object Opening
Fraction of the opening area which can be opened.
Occupancy is an aggregated group of occupants of a usage zone or building unit, which can be residents, workers, visitors etc.

Thermal boundary surfaces are quasi-coplanar surfaces bounding the thermal zone. They may be linked to the gml:BoundarySurface when possible, but not necessary (e.g. cellar ceiling or top storey ceiling in the case of LOD1-3)
Azimuth angle of the normal surface vector. By convention: - azimuth = 0 for north orientation. - Horizontal surface have a azimuth = 0.
Inclination angle of the normal surface vector. By convention, inclination = 0 for horizontal plane.
Application Domain Extension Energy of CityGML object BoundarySurface
Percentaged energy absorptance in different wavelength ranges
Information and properties of a given variable.
Facilities and Appliances inside the usage zone or building unit, which consumes and dissipate energy.
Abstract superclass for all Material classes. A Material is a homogeneous substance that can be used to form elements.
Reference to internal or external information sources.
Energy demand is the useful energy required to satisfy a specific end-use, such as heating, cooling, domestic hot water etc.
Application Domain Extension Energy of CityGML object AbstractBuilding
Floor area [m] considered for the normalization of the standard energy demands.
Facilities for domestic hot water usage.
System storing energy. A same storage may store the energy of different end-users and different end-use.
Percentaged energy transmittance in different wavelength ranges
Final device(s) which deliver the required end-use to the end-user in his end-use place (e.g. radiators or convectors for heating etc.)

Ceiling of the highest storey of the zone.
Determine the level of energy coverage (may be time depending) by a given operation mode of an energy conversion system.
Determines the usage of Construction in terms of the Layer order.
If orientation == true the layers are used in the specified order (see Construction), otherwise in reverse order.
Reference to the Construction being used.
can be from district network /solar systems...
Energy supply is the part of the energy produced by the energy conversion systems which is used to satisfy the end-use demand of a city object.
Electrical appliances inside the building unit or building zone.

This is an X3D element to map a texture to this material. From X3D specification: The ImageTexture node defines a texture map by specifying an image file and general parameters for mapping to geometry. Texture maps are defined in a 2D coordinate system (s, t) that ranges from [0.0, 1.0] in both directions. The bottom edge of the image corresponds to the S-axis of the texture map, and left edge of the image corresponds to the T-axis of the texture map. The lower-left pixel of the image corresponds to s=0, t=0, and the top-right pixel of the image corresponds to s=1, t=1. <!--When fixed: add type="x3d:ImageTexture"-->

From X3D specification: If repeatS is TRUE, the texture map is repeated outside the [0.0, 1.0] texture coordinate range in the S direction so that it fills the shape. If repeatS is FALSE, the texture coordinates are clamped in the S direction to lie within the [0.0, 1.0] range.

From X3D specification: If repeatT is TRUE, the texture map is repeated outside the [0.0, 1.0] texture coordinate range in the T direction so that it fills the shape. If repeatT is FALSE, the texture coordinates are clamped in the T direction to lie within the [0.0, 1.0] range.

Specifies location of the image. From X3D specification: The texture is read from the URL specified by the url field. When the url field contains no values, texturing is disabled. Browsers shall support the JPEG and PNG image file formats. In addition, browsers may support other image formats (e.g. CGM) which can be rendered into a 2D image. Support for the GIF format is also recommended (including transparency).
regular time series contain values generated at regularly spaced interval of time
Energy conversion system is a system producing the energy necessary to satisfy the end-use (or to feed the networks) from an energy source.
give also Efficiency Unit (COP, EEF, W/cfm, %, other)

Reference to layers that comprise this construction. Multiple LayerId's order is important and specifies the layering of the layer's referenced materials. Area of the surface [m], portion of the related thermal boundary surface.
Operation mode details the operation of the energy conversion system for a specific end-use and operation time.
A Layer is a combination of one of more materials, references via a LayerComponent.
Beweegbare of vaste verbinding tussen twee punten, die door water, een weg of anderszins gescheiden zijn. Hiertoe behoren ook viaduct, aquaduct, wildviaduct, en fly-over.

Values: Ja,Nee,zie groep Description: Indicatie of de materile historie van de attribuutsoort te bevragen is (indien van toepassing: als attribuutsoort binnen het groepattribuutsoort). Materile historie geeft aan wanneer een verandering is opgetreden in de werkelijkheid die heeft geleid tot veranderjng van de attribuutwaarde. Met het opnemen van deze indicatie zien we af van de specificatie van ‘historie-attributen’ bij objecttypen, zoals bijvoorbeeld ‘Datum begin geldigheid gegevens’, zoals dat gebruikelijk is in sommige basisregistratiecatalogi. Dergelijke attributen (meta-gegevens) volgen logischerwijs uit deze indicatie. Om duidelijk te maken om welke attribuutsoort in welke basisregistratie het gaat, geven we dit aan in de indicatie. Indien het attribuutsoort deel uit maakt van een groepattribuutsoort dan geldt de specificatie aldaar ook voor het attribuutsoort binnen de groep, zij het op groepsniveau. Een eventuele specificatie bij het attribuutsoort anders dan ‘zie Groep’ geldt dan alleen binnen het groepattribuutsoort.

Values: Ja,Nee,zie groep Description: Indicatie of de formele historie van de attribuutsoort te bevragen is (indien van toepassing: als attribuutsoort binnen het groepattribuutsoort). Dergelijke attributen (meta-gegevens) volgen logsicherwijs uit deze indicatie.
